description: For your next lunch, ditch the Big Mac and go for an equally quick and affordable yet vastly more nutritious and delicious bowl of BiBimBap from Backpackers’ Food Truck. “BiBim” means “mixing” and “Bap” means “steamed rice” in Korean. It’s a bowl of rice topped with various vegetables (including spinach, bean sprouts, carrots, mushrooms, or lettuce, etc..) and topped with an egg or Korean BBQ. You then mix together your bowl with Gochujang (a vibrantly flavorful fermented red chili paste) and sesame oil, and then it’s ready to be enjoyed. The Backpackers also like to refer to BiBimBap as a “bowl of healthiness”, which is perfectly accurate as it contains all the nutrients you need from a meal, with few calories. The profits go straight toward operating the Backpackers’ educational program that teaches children all around Los Angeles about healthy eating.  For your next lunch, be sure to stop by the Backpackers’ Truck and join in their pursuit of healthiness through tasty food!
name: Bibimbap Backpackers
